data.description:
From: PhishLabs Security Operations <not@domain.com>
Subject: =? =?gb2312?Q?ted:_www.icloud.com.agona.cn?=


________________________________
From: west263
Sent: Saturday, November 30, 2019 8:36:41 PM (UTC-05:00) Eastern Time (US & Canada)
To: PhishLabs Security Operations; not@domain.com; not@domain.com
Subject: 回复：[PL-1405082] Malicious domain detected: www.icloud.com.agona.cn

-- External email--


Thank you for allowing us an opportunity to assist you.

We have suspended our customer to use this domain. You can check it later.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us. We look forward to assisting you.

Have a wonderful day!



------------------

Best regards,

Lillian


------------------ 原始邮件 ------------------

发件人:  PhishLabs Security Operations<not@domain.com>;
日  期:  2019-11-30 (星期六) 08:37:19
收件人:  not@domain.com<not@domain.com>;not@domain.com<not@domain.com>;not@domain.com<not@domain.com>;
主  题:  [PL-1405082] Malicious domain detected: www.icloud.com.agona.cn


During an investigation of fraud, we discovered a domain(s) registered for the sole intent of malicious activity, which is being used to attack our client and their customers.

We have addressed this report to the responsible authoritative providers over this website who have the ability to disable the malicious content in question. This includes but is not limited to the hosting provider(s), nameserver, registrar and if applicable, the registry.  Based on your relationship to the content in question or services provided, please see our specific request below.

This threat has been active for at least 2.1 hours.

hXXp www[.]icloud[.]com[.]agona[.]cn/ios/uy930glgr8yx54n4zkcw[.]asp?uy930glgr8yx54n4zkcw=
hXXp www[.]icloud[.]com[.]agona[.]cn/ios/upvf7o4kon1kpt4vfy18[.]asp?upvf7o4kon1kpt4vfy18=
hXXp www[.]icloud[.]com[.]agona[.]cn/ios/vweixhklbjw1t1ve3b4n[.]asp?vweixhklbjw1t1ve3b4n=
hXXp www[.]icloud[.]com[.]agona[.]cn/an3n3abqqtkpuok9vw9c[.]asp?an3n3abqqtkpuok9vw9c

First detection of malicious activity: 11-29-2019 22:26:17 UTC
Most recent observation of malicious activity: 11-30-2019 00:35:06 UTC
Associated IP Addresses: 8.8.8.8

Evidence of malicious content is provided below my signature.

===   HOSTING  PROVIDER AND/OR WEBSITE OWNER    ===
If you agree that this is malicious, we kindly request that you take steps to have the content removed as soon as possible.  It is highly likely that the intruder who set up this phishing content has also left additional fraudulent material on this server such as illegitimate access points.

===   REGISTRAR / REGISTRY   ===
We kindly request that this domain is placed on hold as soon as possible and all client related information sink holed. It is also very likely the registrant in question has registered various other domains through your service and it is suggested you investigate as you see fit.

===   NAMESERVER, SOA   ===
If it is within your power, please consider disabling the routing to this domain to prevent further abuse to the public.

===   CERT/CIRT, ETC.   ===
If you're able to assist in any means possible to see to the termination of this content, please do so.  Your local expertise and influence on this matter is critical to this effort.

If we have contacted you in error, or if there is a better way for us to report this incident, please let us know so that we may continue our investigation.

We are extremely grateful for your assistance.

Kind regards,

Yogender Chauhan
PhishLabs Security Operations
12023866001
Available 24/7


Evidence:
Please see attached screenshot.
.

[PL-1405082]

data.title: Fw: [Pl-1405778] [6e5658a2b054ed4f]: Cloudflare has responded to your phishing report.
data.description:
From: PhishLabs Security Operations <not@domain.com>
Subject: Fw: [Pl-1405778] [6e5658a2b054ed4f]: Cloudflare has responded to your phishing report.

________________________________________
From: Cloudflare Trust & Safety <not@domain.com>
Sent: Saturday, November 30, 2019 13:20
To: PhishLabs Security Operations
Subject: [6e5658a2b054ed4f]: Cloudflare has responded to your phishing report.

-- External email--


Cloudflare received your phishing report regarding:
oxicciw-iw-iwo.pp.ua

Please be aware Cloudflare is a network provider offering a reverse proxy, pass-through security service. We are not a hosting provider. Cloudflare does not control the content of our customers. Access to the submitted phishing URL(s) has been restricted.

Accepted URL(s) on oxicciw-iw-iwo.pp.ua:
google.com/MFZ6ZktBNlI=/

        IP Address: 8.8.8.8

        Hosting Provider:
        -----------------

        SHINJIRU-MY

        Abuse Contact:
        --------------

        not@domain.com



We have notified our customer of your report. We have forwarded your report on to the responsible hosting provider.
You may also direct your report to:

1. The provider where oxicciw-iw-iwo.pp.ua is hosted (provided above);
2. The owner listed in the WHOIS record for oxicciw-iw-iwo.pp.ua and/or;
3. The contact listed on the oxicciw-iw-iwo.pp.ua site.

Note: A lookup of the IP for a Cloudflare customer website will show Cloudflare IPs because we are a pass-through network. The actual website is still hosted at the hosting provider indicated above. If the hosting provider has any questions, please have the hosting provider contact us directly regarding this site. Due to attempted abuse of our complaint reporting process, we will only provide the IP of oxicciw-iw-iwo.pp.ua to the responsible hosting provider if they contact us directly at not@domain.com

Regards,

Cloudflare Abuse
